http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/RIL-donates-Rs.-84-lakh-for-education-sector/article14009629.ece

Representatives of the Reliance Industries Limited (RIL) on Tuesday handed over a cheque for Rs. 84 lakh to East Godavari Collector H. Arun Kumar for the development of education sector.As part of its corporate social responsibility (CSR), the RIL launched ‘Reliance Dhirubhai Ambani Protsaham’ scheme seven years ago as part of which it had been funding Intermediate education of meritorious students from poor financial background in corporate colleges.As the scheme is being implemented through the Social Welfare Department, the cheque was handed over to the Collector.N. Ravichandran (Head, Support Services), M. Nagi Reddy (general manager, HR) and N. Ramana Murthy (senior lead, CSR) were present in the programme.